The paper deals with the problem of efficiently preprocessing high volume bird acoustic data, which involves several existing preprocessing steps including noise reduction approaches. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a distributed computing architecture to improve execution time further supports the possibility of cs.DC being a likely sub-category.
